referred_to_by.content: Collection of the Artist (1900); (Galerie Bernheim Jeune, Paris, France, March 28, 1900, acquired from the artist) (1900); (Galerie Bernheim Jeune, Paris, France, November 26, 1900, sold to Georges Dusseuil) (1900); Georges Dusseuil [1848-1926], Paris France (1900-1902); (Galerie Bernheim Jeune, Paris, France, May 6, 1902, acquired from Georges Dusseuil) (1902-1903); (Galerie Bernheim Jeune, Paris, France, April 29, 1903, sold to Olivier Sainsere) (1903); Olivier Sainsere [1852-1923], Paris, France (1903–?); by descent to his daughter, Jeanne (Sainsère) Richet [1883–1972], Paris, France (by 1923); by descent to her daughter, Jacqueline (Richet) Souchère [1908–1984], Paris, France (by 1972); by descent to her daughter, Jeanne (Souchère) Gelin, Paris, France (by 1984); Galerie Cazeau-Béraudière, Paris, France (before 2002); (Galerie Hopkins-Custot, Paris, France, sold to Nancy F. and Joseph P. Keithley) (2002); Nancy F. and Joseph P. Keithley, Cleveland, OH, given to the Cleveland Museum of Art (2002–2020); The Cleveland Museum of Art, Cleveland, OH (2020–)
